                        neutron”</olink>. The sections in this chapter provide examples of creating a network using each
                API.--></para>
        <para>The following flow chart shows the steps to attach a network and provision a server by using the neutron
                API<!--
                and the nova-network API-->. These steps are detailed in this guide.</para>
        <note>
                <para>There are two ways of passing network attributes to the server at boot time through the nova API. <orderedlist>
                                <listitem>
                                        <para>You can pass the network ID.</para>
                                </listitem>
                                <listitem>
                                        <para>You can pass the ID of the port(s) on the desired network(s).</para>
                                </listitem>
                        </orderedlist> The flowchart assumes that you are passing the port UUID of the Isolated Network in
                        the nova API.</para>
        </note>
